					<description><!--[CDATA[<p-->Editor’s Note: May is National Skin Cancer Awareness Month&nbsp; Skin cancer&nbsp;is the most common cancer in the U.S.&nbsp;&nbsp;More than 6 million adults are treated for it each year, says&nbsp;Dr. Michael Colgan, a Mayo Clinic Health System dermatologist in Eau Claire, Wisconsin. Melanoma is an aggressive form of skin cancer. In 2025, an estimated 104,960 cases […]<p></p>
